      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">The plant sent by Mr. Thos. Hanson, of Glen Thompson, ¶ Vic. ¶  as probably poisonous is botanically known as Minuranthes ¶ Typesetter's misreading of Minuranthus? ¶  gnaphaloides, and belongs to a tr...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.12.08a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Leader</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from 'A suspected poison plant', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leader</seg>, 16 December 1871. p. 7 (B71.12.05). M's text follows a letter from T. Hanson to the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leader, </seg>enclosing a plant suspected of poisoning sheep, and is introduced by 'Having submitted the specimens sent to Baron von Mueller, that gentleman has kindly vouchsafed the following reply:—'.</p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The plant sent by Mr. Thos. Hanson, of Glen Thompson,</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> as probably poisonous is botanically known as Minuranthes</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Typesetter's misreading of</seg> Minuranthus?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> gnaphaloides, and belongs to a tribe of plants (gnaphaloid compositae) not known to be deleterious. Your correspondent might readily put this question at rest by feeding a sheep for some days exclusively on this herb. The sample submitted to me is far too small for any chemical tests.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">Obediently,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/> Ferd. Von Mueller. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">Melbourne Botanical Gardens, 8th December.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Minuranthes%20gnaphaloides">Minuranthes gnaphaloides</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
